"data\";s:4:\"Amir\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2932:\"<p>This release cycle of WordPress 4.0 was a pleasure for us (and many other plugin authors). Betas and release candidates were available well ahead of the official release date, allowing everyone to get ready for it.</p>\n<p>For a few weeks, we&#8217;ve been testing and updating WPML to address the recent changes in WordPress 4.0. WPML 3.1.7, which we released last week, includes all the required updates. Fortunately, these updates are not huge, but it was still important to be prepared for them.</p>\n<p>If you are updating your sites and having trouble, we can help. Please keep in mind that issues that you see, might be coming from different places. Before you report bugs, we recommend turning off other plugins. If possible, you should also temporarily switch to the default theme.</p>\n<p>This new WordPress version introduces changes in the visual editor, as well as in several core functions. Since WordPress, the theme and all plugins run as one PHP process, problems in one place can manifest in different areas. If you see problems in the WordPress admin, we recommend these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open the Javascript console (available in Firefox and Chrome) and see if you spot any Javascript errors</li>\n<li>Enable <a href=\"http://wpml.org/documentation/support/debugging-wpml/\">PHP error logging</a> and see if there are errors there</li>\n<li>Disable plugins and see if problems are resolved</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you need our help, go to the <a href=\"http://wpml.org/forums/forum/english-support/\">WPML technical support forum</a>. Create a new thread as &#8216;I need to resolve a problem&#8217;. Make sure you include the debug information from your site, so that we can see what we are running. In the thread, include screenshots that show the problem. If you see Javascript or PHP errors, paste them.</p>\n<p>Please include the term &#8216;WP 4.0&#8242; in the title, so that we can prioritize and respond to these issues faster.</p>\n<p>BTW, before any update of WordPress, your theme or plugins, we strongly recommend backing up your database. Having a DB backup gives you the peace of mind, knowing that you can always revert changes and that if anything goes wrong, you&#8217;re safe.</p>\n<p>Happy WordPress upgrade!</p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=pOp0coqlt8U:YwH_vr_xPwY:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=pOp0coqlt8U:YwH_vr_xPwY:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=pOp0coqlt8U:YwH_vr_xPwY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=pOp0coqlt8U:YwH_vr_xPwY:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=pOp0coqlt8U:YwH_vr_xPwY:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=pOp0coqlt8U:YwH_vr_xPwY:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/pOp0coqlt8U\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"http://wpml.org/2014/09/wpml-ready-wordpress-4-0-ready/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"6\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"http://wpml.org/2014/09/wpml-ready-wordpress-4-0-ready/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"WooCommerce Pay for Payment and WCML\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/ES2sf1kOD2s/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"http://wpml.org/2014/09/woocommerce-pay-payment-and-wcml/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 02 Sep 2014 13:46:13 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"Compatibility Bulletin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://wpml.org/?p=435739\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:403:\"WooCommerce Pay for Payment http://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-pay-for-payment/ Extension Description Add individual charges for each payment method as a flat rate and/or as a percentage of the cart total. The plug-in first calculates the percentage rate and then adds the fixed rate on top. Fixed Issues Ability to translate the “Extra Charge” items title. Setting Extra Charges New [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Bernat Torras\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3174:\"<h2>WooCommerce Pay for Payment</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-pay-for-payment/\">http://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-pay-for-payment/</a></p>\n<h2>Extension Description</h2>\n<p>Add individual charges for each payment method as a flat rate and/or as a percentage of the cart total. The plug-in first calculates the percentage rate and then adds the fixed rate on top.</p>\n<h2>Fixed Issues</h2>\n<p>Ability to translate the “Extra Charge” items title.</p>\n<h2>Setting Extra Charges</h2>\n<p>New fields were added on each “Payment method” configuration page. These fields allow the user to add an extra charge that will be applied when the customer selects a payment method. It is also possible to customize the label that will appear for this extra charge.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_435741\" style=\"width: 258px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/backend.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-435741 size-medium\" src=\"http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/backend-248x300.png\" alt=\"Setting Extra Charges\" width=\"248\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Setting Extra Charges</p></div>\n<h2>Translating Extra Charges</h2>\n<p>The extra charges titles can be translated directly in WPML&gt;Strings Translation.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_435744\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/st-2.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-435744 size-medium\" src=\"http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/st-2-300x172.png\" alt=\"Translating Extra Charges\" width=\"300\" height=\"172\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Translating Extra Charges</p></div>\n<h2>Frontend</h2>\n<p>When a customer selects an extra-charged payment method, a new row will appear displaying the extra charge title with the extra amount. This field appears translated in secondary languages, and the price is also filtered using the current currency.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_435748\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/checkout.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-435748 size-medium\" src=\"http://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/checkout-300x296.png\" alt=\"Translated Strings in Checkout page\" width=\"300\" height=\"296\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Translated Strings in Checkout page</p></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=ES2sf1kOD2s:c0xZAXl2sQ8:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=ES2sf1kOD2s:c0xZAXl2sQ8:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=ES2sf1kOD2s:c0xZAXl2sQ8:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=ES2sf1kOD2s:c0xZAXl2sQ8:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=ES2sf1kOD2s:c0xZAXl2sQ8:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=ES2sf1kOD2s:c0xZAXl2sQ8:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/ES2sf1kOD2s\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"http://wpml.org/2014/09/woocommerce-pay-payment-and-wcml/feed/\";s: